rComments: She is an amazing professor and really cares about her students. I had no background in finance and not particularly interested, but I was still motivated to go to every class and ended up with a good grade! It's very important to have a good, reliable group since a huge part of the class is the workshops.

Sweetest prof in our department. Takes time to explain concepts and actually wants you to know what you're learning. Not a hard course but still requires time to understand the textbook. COME TO CLASS. Most of the marks are for in-class workshops. Textbook is good for extra info and in-class questions.
Great teacher! Pay attention & you will easily pass!
She's very helpful and kind. Took her time to make sure we understand. The workshops kept us on track with the course.

Very interesting and useful course to take even if you have no background in finance. You learn everything from scratch at a good pace. The professor's aim is to help you learn something by the end of the course, not to fail. If you do the readings, the lectures will be much easier to understand and the workshops will be much better to understand.

She's simply amazing. She cares about you and your grades. Wish all my professors cared as much as she does. Relatively easy course, just simple math and simple accounting, the bulk of which are done using Excel so you bare;y need to do any work yourself

Although this is an overall tough class, she breaks concepts down to terms students can understand. She sets the course in a way where if you try you will succeed. Providing you with knowledge that can be applied in real life situations. She's a kind, fair professor who is willing to help.

rComments: She is so approachable and makes the word finance not scary. She is super passionate about the topics she teaches and cares for the advancement of her students! I have never taken finance courses because it scared me but she changed this perception. Take her class!
